==English==
===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''[[née]]'', feminine of ''[[né]]'', past participle of ''[[naître]]'', to be born

===Adjective===
'''nee'''

#Used when giving the [[maiden name]] of a woman.
#:''Mrs Smith, nee Jones''

====Usage notes====
*As it is not a naturalised word in English, '''nee''' is usually italicised.

====Forms and variants====
*[[née]]

